<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="162" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,188,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[849,912,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">nigri-</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[970,1082,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="162">macularis</emphasis>
, referring to the diffused black triangular patch on the dorsum of the forewing.
</paragraph>
